		</div>
		
		
		
		<hr class="show-hr1">	
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1 show-map" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/50/San_Marino_in_Europe.svg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Republic of San Marino is a micro state on 23 square miles (61 square kilometers) inside of Italy. It is the oldest country in the world. San Marino was named after Saint Marinus, a stonemason. In 301 AD Marinus was fleeing the persecution of the Catholics by the Roman Emperor when he found a small monastic community on top of Monte Titano in San Marino and settled there. In 1625 San Marino became an enclave within the Papal States. In the 19th century San Marino served as a refuge for many people in favor of Italian Unification. 
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://rossiwrites.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/St.-Marinus-holding-the-republic-he-founded-San-Marino-rossiwrites.com_.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Saint Marinus, founder of San Marino</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Although San Marino was mostly neutral in World War I, the aftermath of the war caused a big class difference between lower and middle class. This led to the development of the Sammarinese Fascist Party, who ruled until 1944. After which time San Marino’s government became the world’s only democratically elected communist government with Sammarinese Communist and Fascist party working in coalition.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Today San Marino has a constitution that dictates the parliament must choose two Captains Regent (heads of state) every six months. The Captain Regents have equal powers and can be exercised within the parliamentary legislation.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="http://admin.abc.sm/img/gallery/upload/422/img_lastminute_264678.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Investiture Ceremony of the Captain Regents, a public holiday in San Marino</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The country’ economy is based on finance and tourism. It is one of the wealthiest countries in the world with a stable economy, no national debt and lowest unemployment.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Geographically San Marino is a mountainous enclave inside Italy. It is one of the only three countries in the world that is enclosed by another country (the other countries are Vatican City and Lesotho). It is the third smallest country in Europe after Vatican City and Monaco.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.state.gov/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/San-Marino-2117x1406.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>City of San Marino, San Marino</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<h3 class="show-factsh3">
				Two unique facts about San Marino
			</h3>
		</div>
			
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Military of San Marino is the smallest military in the world and is made of Italian Armed Forces. It has different divisions like border patrol, mount guard at government buildings and assisting police in major criminal cases. The Guard of the Rock is a division of military responsible for border patrol as well as guarding the Palazzo Pubblico in San Marino City. They are most visible to tourists and are known for their colorful uniforms and their ceremonies of Changing of the Guards.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/15b084_1dfdf058b5e942f79e3107afdd53944c~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_1000,h_668,al_c,q_90,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01/15b084_1dfdf058b5e942f79e3107afdd53944c~mv2.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Palazzo Pubblico in City of San Marino</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				San Marino has an infamous Museum of Torture with a collection of medieval torture weapons that were used in the area thousand years ago.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
